GeoPulse 2.0 – AI Visibility & Retrieval Intelligence Platform
Executive Summary
Generative Engine Optimization (GEO) focuses on making your content discoverable, understandable, and cited by AI systems. Unlike classic SEO, which seeks rankings on search engine results pages, GEO aims to make your content part of the answer when users ask questions of AI search engines such as ChatGPT, Gemini, Perplexity or Google AI Overviews.
Recent research shows that AI search engines break user prompts into sub-queries, retrieve relevant passages using retrieval-augmented generation (RAG), synthesize answers and provide citations. Your goal is to be one of those cited sources. You achieve this by ensuring technical crawlability, semantic structure, authoritative content, prompt‑oriented research and continuous measurement of AI visibility.
GeoPulse 2.0 expands beyond a simple ‘AI readiness score’ to become a comprehensive AI visibility & retrieval intelligence platform. It introduces a transparent scoring model, retrieval simulation, industry‑specific recommendations, demand & conversion metrics, and robust reporting to help organisations capture demand from AI search and convert it into revenue.
