2. Key Deficiencies in GeoPulse 1.0
•	The original GeoPulse report treats HTTP 403/401 errors as content failures, conflating blocked access with poor structure. This leads to false negatives and undermines trust.
•	Opaque scoring: site‑level scores are presented without disclosing the full rubric or how page checks aggregate. Users cannot understand how to improve their scores.
•	Undefined metrics: terms like ‘E‑E‑A‑T signals’ and ‘extractability’ are not operationally defined or tied to detection logic.
•	Generic recommendations: advice such as ‘add schema’ or ‘add Q&A’ is not mapped to specific pages or industries.
•	No aggregation of insights: pages are listed individually without identifying site‑wide patterns or template‑level issues.
•	Lacks demand and conversion layers: the report does not analyse which queries matter or whether traffic converts to leads or revenue.
•	No benchmarking or validation against peer sites or visibility outcomes; the score lacks context.
