5. Status Model & Scoring Framework
GeoPulse 2.0 introduces a robust evaluation state model. Each check returns a status from the following set:
•	PASS: The criterion was evaluated successfully and met.
•	FAIL: The criterion was evaluated successfully but did not meet the standard.
•	BLOCKED: The crawler could not access the resource (e.g., HTTP 403/401, robots disallow). These do not affect scores but require whitelisting.
•	NOT_EVALUATED: The check was not applicable (e.g., no videos, no forms).
•	LOW_CONFIDENCE: The signal was ambiguous; manual review recommended.
•	WARNING: Non‑critical issue that may impede AI visibility (e.g., missing alt text).
•	Scoring philosophy: Each category receives a score from 0–100 based on weighted sub‑metrics. Categories include AI Readiness (crawl & rendering), Extractability, Trust, Demand Coverage and Conversion Readiness.
•	Page‑level scores roll up into template‑level and site‑wide scores via weighted averaging, adjusting for page importance (traffic, conversion value).
•	BLOCKED checks are excluded from scoring; NOT_EVALUATED checks are neutral; LOW_CONFIDENCE checks are included with half‑weight.
•	An overall score summarises all categories but is accompanied by category scores to provide diagnostic granularity.
