7. Detection Methods & Data Flow
•	Crawlers interact with the site using both raw HTTP and headless browsers to capture server‑rendered HTML and fully rendered DOM.
•	A parsing engine extracts headings, paragraphs, lists, tables and schema markup. It computes chunk sizes and answer density, highlights questions framed as headings and identifies stand‑alone answer sentences.
•	A schema validator checks JSON‑LD types and properties; misaligned or missing schema triggers specific recommendations.
•	LLM classifiers evaluate author bios, credential statements and external citations, flagging missing trust signals.
•	Retrieval simulation uses RAG to ask representative prompts; retrieved passages are compared with ground truth to detect hallucinations and measure extractability.
•	Prompt mining modules crawl forums (Reddit, Quora) and generative search results to identify recurring question patterns and cluster them by topic and intent.
•	Conversion audit scripts scan for forms, CTAs, analytics tags and funnel flows to measure conversion readiness.
8. Recommendation Engine & Industry Overlays
Recommendations are generated at three levels: page‑specific, template‑level and site‑wide. Each recommendation is contextualised by industry and prioritised by impact vs effort.
Healthcare: emphasise MedicalOrganization and MedicalWebPage schema, cite government or peer‑reviewed sources, include author credentials and clinic licensing information.
Legal: use LegalService and Attorney schema, provide case law citations, disclose bar memberships and highlight privacy compliance.
Financial services: include FinancialProduct and InvestmentFund schema, ensure risk disclosures, link to regulatory filings and demonstrate fiduciary credentials.
B2B SaaS: implement SoftwareApplication and Service schema, provide customer testimonials, pricing pages, and emphasise integration capabilities.
For each missing schema or trust signal, the engine supplies a code snippet (e.g., JSON‑LD) and clarifies which pages require insertion.
9. Reporting & UX Design
The report begins with an executive summary highlighting overall and category scores, top issues and recommended next steps.
Site‑wide findings are presented as matrices showing how many pages pass or fail each check. Drill‑downs allow users to see which templates or URLs deviate from averages.
Template analysis groups pages by type (e.g., homepage, service page, blog post) to identify systemic problems and avoid repetitive lists.
Per‑URL exceptions are highlighted only when they diverge significantly from the template pattern.
Each recommendation includes an effort vs impact rating and a suggested owner (developer, content writer, marketer).
Reports are available as interactive dashboards and machine‑readable exports (CSV, JSON). Enterprise tiers integrate with project management (Jira) and CMS platforms for streamlined implementation.
